"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"value":"Factor","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"table-cell"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"value":"Comments","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"table-cell"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"value":"Timing Impact","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"table-cell"}],"nodeType":"table-row"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Certain people oppose the freeze","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"table-cell"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"A freeze is likely to be controversial, therefore a freeze softfork may only gain an appropriate level of consensus, when we are relatively close to Qday","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"table-cell"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Push the freeze date later","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"table-cell"}],"nodeType":"table-row"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Avoid coin loss of people being too slow to plan for the freeze","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"table-cell"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"We likely need a large gap between when the freeze softfork activates and the freeze itself activates, so that people have time to move their coins. People could have coins in deep cold storage, be unaware of the quantum related news or even have timelocks","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"table-cell"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Push the freeze date later","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"table-cell"}],"nodeType":"table-row"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Want to avoid coin loss as a result of the freeze being activated after Qday","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"table-cell"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"If the freeze date is too late, millions of coins could be stolen. Therefore, perhaps we need a large margin of safety between the expected Qday and the activation of the freeze","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"table-cell"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Push the freeze date earlier","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"table-cell"}],"nodeType":"table-row"}],"nodeType":"table"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"In addition to there being conflicting considerations, pushing time pressure in opposing directions, it is not like we just need to settle on just one date. There are potentially four dates to consider, as the below image illustrates.","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"underline"}],"value":"Illustrative Coin Freeze Timeline","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{"target":{"sys":{"id":"5mUP85zIximxe9n38eOTML","type":"Link","linkType":"Asset"}}},"content":[],"nodeType":"embedded-asset-block"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Given the uncertainty over when or if Qday will ever happen and the long time horizon that is likely to be required to get a freeze to work effectively, while respecting Bitcoin's censorship resistance properties as much as possible, there is probably considerable risk that the final freeze happens either far too late or far too early. Perhaps many years too late or many years too early.","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"One of the fantastic properties of the tapleaf quantum approach is that the new taproot quantum type should never be frozen. At least we would oppose any freeze associated with the new quantum safe Taproot type, even the quantum vulnerable paths, until after Qday. The idea here is that this is a new output type designed for quantum safety and that users who have upgraded here are prepared for quantum computers.","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Therefore, people can continue to spend their coins in a quantum vulnerable way, using the quantum vulnerable tapleaf, almost right up until Qday. With this approach, it doesn't matter as much if the safety buffer period was too long, with quantum development being unexpectedly stalled for decades, because people can continue spending Bitcoin using the efficient quantum vulnerable tapleaf. Once Qday finally happens, the final transition should be relatively easy, with people just needing to be aware to select the quantum safe spend path in their wallets. After Qday, the wallets could be upgraded, with the quantum vulnerable spend path options removed from the GUI. Eventually, there could be a post Qday softfork banning the use of the quantum vulnerable path.","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}]},"category":"Research","categories":["Research"],"languageList":["English"],"imageUrl":"https://images.ctfassets.net/4d5b2rvh73n7/39BJ5tpSVBDr7pzrFb3xwp/247d96ac74c8ef9bd50564891cd7d7dc/qd.jpg","tags":[],"actualLocale":"en-US","seoMetaTitle":null,"seoMetaDescription":null,"customDisclaimer":null}],"featuredPost":{"id":"32nVFFpuZoVCuAvRCdwOR","title":"February BMEX Burn Report ","slug":"bmex-burn-feb-report","publishDate":"2026-02-20T00:00:00.000+08:00","author":"BitMEX","excerpt":"On 2 Feb, BitMEX launched the monthly token burning to create a continuous utility ecosystem for BMEX holders.\n","body":{"nodeType":"document","content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"dat