ta":{},"content":[{"nodeType":"paragraph","data":{},"content":[{"nodeType":"text","value":"New quantum safe output","marks":[],"data":{}}]}]},{"nodeType":"table-cell","data":{},"content":[{"nodeType":"paragraph","data":{},"content":[{"nodeType":"text","value":"0","marks":[],"data":{}}]}]},{"nodeType":"table-cell","data":{},"content":[{"nodeType":"paragraph","data":{},"content":[{"nodeType":"text","value":"0.0%","marks":[],"data":{}}]}]},{"nodeType":"table-cell","data":{},"content":[{"nodeType":"paragraph","data":{},"content":[{"nodeType":"text","value":"None required","marks":[],"data":{}}]}]}]},{"nodeType":"table-row","data":{},"content":[{"nodeType":"table-cell","data":{},"content":[{"nodeType":"paragraph","data":{},"content":[{"nodeType":"text","value":"Total","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"data":{}}]}]},{"nodeType":"table-cell","data":{},"content":[{"nodeType":"paragraph","data":{},"content":[{"nodeType":"text","value":"19,976,207","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"data":{}}]}]},{"nodeType":"table-cell","data":{},"content":[{"nodeType":"paragraph","data":{},"content":[{"nodeType":"text","value":"100.0%","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"data":{}}]}]},{"nodeType":"table-cell","data":{},"content":[{"nodeType":"paragraph","data":{},"content":[{"nodeType":"text","value":"","marks":[],"data":{}}]}]}]}]},{"nodeType":"paragraph","data":{},"content":[{"nodeType":"text","value":"Source: ","marks":[{"type":"superscript"}],"data":{}},{"nodeType":"hyperlink","data":{"uri":"https://dune.com/murchandamus/bitcoins-utxo-set"},"content":[{"nodeType":"text","value":"https://dune.com/murchandamus/bitcoins-utxo-set","marks":[{"type":"superscript"}],"data":{}}]},{"nodeType":"text","value":"","marks":[],"data":{}}]},{"nodeType":"paragraph","data":{},"content":[{"nodeType":"text","value":"These possible post-quantum freeze recovery systems are not without their downsides. For example they may be complicated, involve significant softfork protocol upgrades and be burdensome on node operators, including new possible DoS vulnerabilities. However, if we are going to do a freeze, they may at least be something worth considering. At least it is an interesting thought experiment.","marks":[],"data":{}}]}]},"category":"Research","categories":["Research"],"languageList":["English"],"imageUrl":"https://images.ctfassets.net/4d5b2rvh73n7/617flrmBVLFBeOvNN83Erb/89260814ec320e282a47c981ceb76074/image.png","tags":[],"actualLocale":"en-US","seoMetaTitle":null,"seoMetaDescription":null,"customDisclaimer":null},{"id":"6Pv2bU4zdQAbM22ba2Qfop","title":"What Is Hyperliquid? Complete Beginner's Guide","slug":"what-is-hyperliquid","publishDate":"2026-02-06T00:00:00.000+08:00","author":"BitMEX","excerpt":"Hyperliquid is a self-custodial DEX processing $1-3 billion daily. Here's what traders need to know about trading perpetuals whilst keeping your keys. Now copyable on BitMEX.\n","body":{"nodeType":"document","content":[{"nodeType":"paragraph","data":{},"content":[{"nodeType":"text","value":"Where you trade is just as important as how you trade.","marks":[],"data":{}}]},{"nodeType":"paragraph","data":{},"content":[{"nodeType":"text","value":"If youre looking for speed and liquidity, go for a Centralised Exchange (CEX). If self custody and transparency is a higher priority, go for a Decentralised Exchange (DEX).","marks":[],"data":{}}]},{"nodeType":"paragraph","data":{},"content":[{"nodeType":"text","value":"Whilst no DEX can replace a CEX, Hyperliquid is the closest contender: an L1 blockchain built for trading that delivers CEX-like performance with the power of on-chain.","marks":[],"data":{}}]},{"nodeType":"paragraph","data":{},"content":[{"nodeType":"text","value":"Is this the future of finance? In this guide, well break down:","marks":[],"data":{}}]},{"nodeType":"unordered-list","data":{},"content":[{"nodeType":"list-item","data":{},"content":[{"nodeType":"paragraph","data":{},"content":[{"nodeType":"text","value":"What is Hyperliquid","marks":[],"data":{}}]}]},{"nodeType":"list-item","data":{},"content":[{"nodeType":"paragraph","data":{},"content":[{"nodeType":"text","value":"How Hyperliquid works","marks":[],"data":{}}]}]},{"nodeType":"list-item","data":{},"content":[{"nodeType":"paragraph","data":{},"content":[{"nodeType":"text","value":"How does it compared with other PerpDEX","marks":[],"data":{}}]}]},{"nodeType":"list-item","data":{},"content":[{"nodeType":"paragraph","data":{},"content":[{"nodeType":"text","value":"The risks and mitigations\n","marks":[],"data":{}}]}]}]},{"nodeType":"heading-2","data":{},"content":[{"nodeType":"text","value":"What Is Hyperliquid?","marks":[],"data":{}}]},{"nodeType":"paragraph","data":{},"content":[{"nodeType":"text","value":"Hyperliquid is a Layer 1 Blockchain that hosts a decentralised perpetual futures exchange where you trade with leverage whilst maintaining custody of your funds. No KYC. No withdrawal limits.","marks":[],"data":{}}]},{"nodeType":"paragraph","data":{},"content":[{"nodeType":"text","value":"The platform processes $4-7 billion in daily volume across 50+ perpetual markets. It's built on its own Layer-1 blockchain by ex-MIT and Hudson River Trading engineers who prioritised one thing: matching CEX performance without CEX risk.","marks":[],"data":{}}]},{"nodeType":"paragraph","data":{},"content":[{"nodeType":"text","value":"Unlike other DEXs, Hyperliquid utilises an on-chain Central Limit Order Book (CLOB) instead of a Automated Market Maker (AMM) model found on Uniswap (where liquidity providers passively pool assets).","marks":[],"data":{}}]},{"nodeType":"paragraph","data":{},"content":[{"nodeType":"text","value":"Why this matters","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"data":{}},{"nodeType":"text","value":": Hyperliquid processes up to 200,000 orders per second with a sub-second latency with zero gas fees for placing or cancelling orders  whilst your funds never leave your wallet.","marks":[],"data":{}}]},{"nodeType":"paragraph","data":{},"content":[{"nodeType":"text","value":"BitMEX now offers copy trading for Hyperliquid strategies. You get exposure to top Hyperliquid traders without managing a Web3 wallet yourself. We'll explain how later.\n","marks":[],"data":{}}]},{"nodeType":"heading-2","data":{},"content":[{"nodeType":"text","value":"How Hyperliquid Works","marks":[],"data":{}}]},{"nodeType":"heading-3","data":{},"content":[{"nodeType":"text","value":"HyperBFT Consensus","marks":[],"data":{}}]},{"nodeType":"paragraph","data":{},"content":[{"nodeType":"text","value":"Hyperliquid operates on a custom Layer-1 blockchain. Not Ethereum. Not Solana. Their own chain using HyperBFT consensus.","marks":[],"data":{}}]},{"nodeType":"paragraph","data":{},"content":[{"nodeType":"text","value":"Most blockchains function synchronously  validators must agree on a block before starting the next block. HyperBFT allows for optimistic responsive, meaning that the network processes transactions as fast as the validators can communicate. The difference? Trade execution speeds rival off-chain matching engines and solving the latency issues that plagued earlier generations of DEXs.","marks":[],"data":{}}]},{"nodeType":"heading-3","data":{},"content":[{"nodeType":"text","value":"HyperEVM","marks":[],"data":{}}]},{"nodeType":"paragraph","data":{},"content":[{"nodeType":"text","value":"In 2025, Hyperliquid introduces HyperEVM which allows developers to build custom smart contracts that interact directly with the perps exchange.","marks":[],"data":{}}]},{"nodeType":"paragraph","data":{},"content":[{"nodeType":"text","value":"Imagine building a lending protocol that can instantly tap into a DEX with deep liquidity without needing a slow cross chain bridge. The upgrade bridges high frequency trading and programmable finance.","marks":[],"data":{}}]},{"nodeType":"paragraph","data":{},"content":[{"nodeType":"text","value":"At the heart of the Hyperliquid ecosystem, runs two core components: the HLP vault and the HYPE token.","marks":[],"data":{}}]},{"nodeType":"ordered-list","data"